04/01/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic met on Wednesday (January 3rd) with representatives of the Serb People's Council (SNV) and the Serb Refugees' Associations of Croatia, to discuss problems confronting the Serb minority in the country.
SNV leader Milorad Pupovac says the talks focused on reconstruction issues and the reintegration of returnees, former tenancy rights holders, war crimes cases and missing persons.
Serb Refugees' Associations representative Milojko Budimir said they requested an acceleration of exhumation activities and identification of victims missing since the conflict.
(Poslovni dnevnik, Vecernji list, Vjesnik - 04/01/07;
HINA, Beta - 03/01/07)
